Phase 2: Forward Testing (3 Months)
Goal: Validate with real money (micro lots)

Position Sizing Formula:
Risk per trade = 0.5% (first month) → 1.0% (months 2-3)
Position Size = (Account × Risk%) / (Entry - Stop)
Example: $10,000 × 0.5% = $50 risk
        Stop distance = 200 pips ($20 per pip?)
        Position size = $50 / $20 = 2.5 micro lots
Weekly Review Metrics:

Sharpe Ratio > 1.0 = good

Max Drawdown < 15% = acceptable

Win Rate 40-60% = normal

Profit Factor > 1.5 = excellent

Average R-Multiple > 1.0 = good

Critical Success Factors:
1. Market Awareness

Track NFP, FOMC, CPI releases

Avoid trading 30 min before/after major news

Note central bank speeches

2. Psychological Discipline

Take ALL signals (no cherry-picking)

Follow exit rules strictly

Journal your emotional state

3. Continuous Improvement

Review losing trades in detail

Optimize parameters monthly (not daily)

Add new filters based on market evolution

4. Risk Management Rules

Maximum 2 trades per day

Maximum 5% drawdown per week = stop trading

Increase position size only after 20 winning trades

Performance Targets for 6-Month Test:
Metric	Target	Stretch Goal
Net Profit	+5%	+15%
Sharpe Ratio	1.2	1.8
Max Drawdown	<10%	<5%
Win Rate	45%	55%
Profit Factor	1.3	1.8
Trades/Month	15-20	20-25
